(25, 1, '2014-04-08 14:04:03', '2014-04-08 14:04:03', '<h1>Strategic Efficiency</h1>\r\n<div class="col-md-6">\r\nThe continuing financial crisis, combined with the mounting debt problems of the world’s largest economies, is causing ongoing market uncertainty for large financial institutions.  Strategic changes are required if banks are to raise their ROE back into double figures. But strategic changes must also be translated into effective action – something that is often easier said than done.\r\n\r\nAn effective Enterprise Project Portfolio Management (EPPM) solution can create a virtuous circle between strategy formulation and strategy execution, creating an environment in which strategy is turned into KPIs and KPIs into business initiatives that are implemented, managed and monitored in an effective and consistent fashion. \r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="col-md-6">By aligning strategy and execution, an EPPM solution can help financial institutions:\r\n<ul class="list-unstyled custom-list">\r\n	<li>Ensure resources and budgets are aligned with strategic objectives</li>\r\n	<li>Identify and capitalize on growth opportunities</li>\r\n	<li>Measure the performance and value of projects against strategic objectives</li>\r\n<li>Measure the performance and value of projects against strategic objectives</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nBrowse the resources below to see how a world-class EPPM solution can translate strategic aims into effective action – and monitor the results of those actions to inform future strategy changes.\r\n\r\n</div>', 'Strategic Efficiency', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'strategic-efficiency', '', '', '2014-04-23 09:23:26', '2014-04-23 09:23:26', '', 0, 'http://oracle.mointernational-clients.co.uk/?page_id=25', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(26, 1, '2014-04-08 14:03:50', '2014-04-08 14:03:50', '<div class="col-md-6">\r\n\r\nThe continuing financial crisis in some geographies, combined with the mounting debt problems of the world’s largest economies, is causing ongoing market uncertainty for large financial institutions. Strategic changes are required if banks are to raise their ROE back into double figures. But strategic changes must also be translated into effective action - something that is often easier said than done.\r\n\r\nAn effective Enterprise Project Portfolio Management (EPPM) solution can create a virtuous circle between strategy formulation and strategy execution, creating an environment in which strategy is turned into KPIs and KPIs into business initiatives that are implemented, managed and monitored in an effective and consistent fashion.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class="col-md-6">\r\nBy aligning strategy and execution, an EPPM solution can help financial institutions to:\r\n\r\n<ul class="list-unstyled custom-list">\r\n<li>Ensure resources and budgets are aligned with strategic objectives Identify and capitalise on growth opportunities</li>\r\n<li>Boost operating efficiency and reduce operating costs</li>\r\n<li>Increase margins and return on equity</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nBrowse the resources below to see how a world-class EPPM solution can translate strategic aims into effective action - and monitor the results of those actions to inform future strategy changes.\r\n</div>', 'Strategic Efficiency', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '25-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-04-08 14:03:50', '2014-04-08 14:03:50', '', 25, 'http://oracle.mointernational-clients.co.uk/uncategorized/25-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
