(42, 2, '2014-04-11 08:21:53', '2014-04-11 08:21:53', '<div class="col-md-6">Faced with technologically-savvy consumers and agile new competitors, financial services organizations are increasingly looking to their internal IT functions to design and deliver innovative new services. But in fast-changing environment, how can you identify and prioritize the innovations that will meet the organization’s strategic objectives and deliver the best returns?An Enterprise Project Portfolio Management (EPPM) solution can help your IT organization to balance technological innovation with the need to maintain and develop existing, business-critical systems. With a clearer view of all assets across the enterprise, IT functions can improve project selection, execution, and success-while optimizing resources to support continued innovation.</div>\n<div class="col-md-6">Oracle’s Instantis EnterpriseTrack is a leading, cloud-based PPM solution that can help you to:\n<ul class="list-unstyled custom-list">\n	<li>Deliver winning products and services</li>\n	<li>Prioritize the most promising development projects</li>\n	<li>Optimize work and resource management</li>\n	<li>Facilitate continuous improvement</li>\n</ul>\nExplore the resources below to discover how EPPM is enabling financial institutions to deliver true service innovation.\n\n</div>', 'Service Innovation', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '13-autosave-v1', '', '', '2014-04-11 08:21:53', '2014-04-11 08:21:53', '', 13, 'http://oracle.mointernational-clients.co.uk/uncategorized/13-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(43, 2, '2014-04-17 09:36:14', '2014-04-17 09:36:14', '<h1>Regulatory Mastery</h1>\n<div class="col-md-6">One of the consequences of the financial crisis has been a tighter regulatory environment and more intense scrutiny, leaving banks and insurers struggling to keep pace with the accelerating introduction of new regulations. \n\nThis presents many challenges for Risk and Compliance functions. They must interpret new regulations correctly; understand where they should be applied; communicate the required changes across the organization; ensure the changes are made; and demonstrate their existence and effectiveness to the relevant regulator. All while making optimum use of the often limited budget and resources available for compliance initiatives. \n\n</div>\n<div class="col-md-6">With its centralized, portfolio-driven approach, an EPPM solution can enable Risk and Compliance professionals to:\n<ul class="list-unstyled custom-list">\n	<li>Plan and execute compliance strategies centrally</li>\n	<li>Enable full visibility and collaboration around compliance initiatives</li>\n	<li>Efficiently manage, allocate and track compliance resources and budgets</li>\n	<li>•	Minimize compliance costs and risks</li>\n</ul>\nTo discover more about how EPPM can enable your organization to achieve regulatory mastery in a fast-changing world, browse the resources below.\n\n</div>', 'Regulatory Mastery', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '28-autosave-v1', '', '', '2014-04-17 09:36:14', '2014-04-17 09:36:14', '', 28, 'http://oracle.mointernational-clients.co.uk/uncategorized/28-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
