(70, 2, '2014-04-17 09:26:26', '2014-04-17 09:26:26', '<h1>FSI Overview</h1>\r\n<div class="col-md-6">At the same time, disruptive new entrants are capturing market share with innovative online and mobile products. Established financial services organizations must develop new offers to maintain competitive advantage. To do so, they need to innovate while ensuring service quality meets customer expectations. \r\n\r\nFinally, regulators are making compliance tougher. Governments and international bodies are introducing new rules and modifying existing ones at an accelerating rate. Financial organizations must be able to keep up with the changes on a global basis, ensure they are implemented, and demonstrate effective risk management.\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="col-md-6">Financial services firms need to be on top of a complex array of projects and priorities in order to stave off new competitors, meet compliance obligations, and impress new and existing customers. Enterprise Project Portfolio Management (EPPM) answers these challenges by putting executives in command of a multitude of strategic initiatives and measuring performance against strategic goals. \r\n\r\nExplore the resources on this site to discover how EPPM is enabling financial services organizations to stay ahead in a rapidly changing business environment.\r\n</div>', 'FSI Overview', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '36-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-04-17 09:26:26', '2014-04-17 09:26:26', '', 36, 'http://oracle.mointernational-clients.co.uk/uncategorized/36-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(71, 2, '2014-04-17 09:33:57', '2014-04-17 09:33:57', '<h1>Strategic Efficiency</h1>\n<div class="col-md-6">\nThe continuing financial crisis, combined with the mounting debt problems of the world’s largest economies, is causing ongoing market uncertainty for large financial institutions.  Strategic changes are required if banks are to raise their ROE back into double figures. But strategic changes must also be translated into effective action – something that is often easier said than done.\n\nAn effective Enterprise Project Portfolio Management (EPPM) solution can create a virtuous circle between strategy formulation and strategy execution, creating an environment in which strategy is turned into KPIs and KPIs into business initiatives that are implemented, managed and monitored in an effective and consistent fashion. \n\n</div>\n<div class="col-md-6">By aligning strategy and execution, an EPPM solution can help financial institutions:\n<ul class="list-unstyled custom-list">\n	<li>Ensure resources and budgets are aligned with strategic objectives</li>\n	<li>Identify and capitalize on growth opportunities</li>\n	<li>Measure the performance and value of projects against strategic objectives</li>\n<li>Measure the performance and value of projects against strategic objectives</li>\n</ul>\nBrowse the resources below to see how a world-class EPPM solution can translate strategic aims into effective action – and monitor the results of those actions to inform future strategy changes.\n\n</div>', 'Strategic Efficiency', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '25-autosave-v1', '', '', '2014-04-17 09:33:57', '2014-04-17 09:33:57', '', 25, 'http://oracle.mointernational-clients.co.uk/uncategorized/25-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(72, 2, '2014-04-17 09:34:02', '2014-04-17 09:34:02', '<h1>Strategic Efficiency</h1>\r\n<div class="col-md-6">\r\nThe continuing financial crisis, combined with the mounting debt problems of the world’s largest economies, is causing ongoing market uncertainty for large financial institutions.  Strategic changes are required if banks are to raise their ROE back into double figures. But strategic changes must also be translated into effective action – something that is often easier said than done.\r\n\r\nAn effective Enterprise Project Portfolio Management (EPPM) solution can create a virtuous circle between strategy formulation and strategy execution, creating an environment in which strategy is turned into KPIs and KPIs into business initiatives that are implemented, managed and monitored in an effective and consistent fashion. \r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="col-md-6">By aligning strategy and execution, an EPPM solution can help financial institutions:\r\n<ul class="list-unstyled custom-list">\r\n	<li>Ensure resources and budgets are aligned with strategic objectives</li>\r\n	<li>Identify and capitalize on growth opportunities</li>\r\n	<li>Measure the performance and value of projects against strategic objectives</li>\r\n<li>Measure the performance and value of projects against strategic objectives</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nBrowse the resources below to see how a world-class EPPM solution can translate strategic aims into effective action – and monitor the results of those actions to inform future strategy changes.\r\n\r\n</div>', 'Strategic Efficiency', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '25-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-04-17 09:34:02', '2014-04-17 09:34:02', '', 25, 'http://oracle.mointernational-clients.co.uk/uncategorized/25-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(73, 2, '2014-04-17 09:35:09', '2014-04-17 09:35:09', '<h1>Service Innovation</h1>\r\n<div class="col-md-6">\r\n\r\nFaced with technologically-savvy consumers and agile new competitors, financial services organizations are increasingly looking to design and deliver innovative new services. But in a fast-changing environment, how can you identify and prioritize the innovations that will meet the organization’s strategic objectives and deliver the best returns?\r\n\r\nAn Enterprise Project Portfolio Management (EPPM) solution can help your organization balance technological innovation with the need to maintain and develop existing, business-critical systems. With a clearer view of all assets across the enterprise, IT and business functions can improve project selection, execution, and success—while optimizing resources to support continued innovation.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="col-md-6">\r\n\r\nOracle’s EnterpriseTrack is a leading, cloud-based PPM solution that can help you to:\r\n<ul class="list-unstyled custom-list">\r\n	<li>Prioritize the most promising development projects</li>\r\n	<li>Optimize work and resource management</li>\r\n	<li>Facilitate continuous improvement</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nExplore the resources below to discover how EPPM is enabling financial institutions to deliver true service innovation.\r\n\r\n</div>', 'Service Innovation', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '13-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-04-17 09:35:09', '2014-04-17 09:35:09', '', 13, 'http://oracle.mointernational-clients.co.uk/uncategorized/13-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(74, 2, '2014-04-17 09:36:20', '2014-04-17 09:36:20', '<h1>Regulatory Mastery</h1>\r\n<div class="col-md-6">One of the consequences of the financial crisis has been a tighter regulatory environment and more intense scrutiny, leaving banks and insurers struggling to keep pace with the accelerating introduction of new regulations. \r\n\r\nThis presents many challenges for Risk and Compliance functions. They must interpret new regulations correctly; understand where they should be applied; communicate the required changes across the organization; ensure the changes are made; and demonstrate their existence and effectiveness to the relevant regulator. All while making optimum use of the often limited budget and resources available for compliance initiatives. \r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="col-md-6">With its centralized, portfolio-driven approach, an EPPM solution can enable Risk and Compliance professionals to:\r\n<ul class="list-unstyled custom-list">\r\n	<li>Plan and execute compliance strategies centrally</li>\r\n	<li>Enable full visibility and collaboration around compliance initiatives</li>\r\n	<li>Efficiently manage, allocate and track compliance resources and budgets</li>\r\n	<li>Minimize compliance costs and risks</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nTo discover more about how EPPM can enable your organization to achieve regulatory mastery in a fast-changing world, browse the resources below.\r\n\r\n</div>', 'Regulatory Mastery', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '28-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-04-17 09:36:20', '2014-04-17 09:36:20', '', 28, 'http://oracle.mointernational-clients.co.uk/uncategorized/28-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
